Chelsea have received bad news from Fenerbahce, as Victor Moses who is on loan with the Turkish side, has picked up an injury. Moses was replaced by Ferdi Kadıoglu in the 77th minute of Fenerbahce’s 5-0 win over Gazisehir Gaziantep FK on Monday. And it has been confirmed that the substitution by Ersun Yanal was not tactical. Fenerbahce have released a statement saying Moses has suffered ruptured muscle, which was detected after the medical examinations. The Yellow Canaries have not disclosed the winger’s possible return date, but such injuries have a minimum recovery period of four weeks. The 28-year-old has made 15 appearances in total in the Super Lig, since his arrival in Turkey in the January transfer window. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.